name: Operation Ivy
description: Operation Ivy was an American punk rock and ska band formed in Berkeley, California, in 1987, consisting of Jesse Michaels (vocals), Tim Armstrong (guitar), Matt Freeman (bass), and Dave Mello (drums). The band was highly influential in the East Bay punk scene and was pivotal to the early success of Lookout Records. They released only one studio album, *Energy* (1989), before disbanding that same year. Despite their short career, Operation Ivy's fusion of ska and hardcore left a lasting impact and they are recognized as a direct precursor to the band Rancid.

name: Jesse Michaels
description: Jesse Michaels is an American singer, songwriter, and artist, most recognized as the co-founder and lead vocalist of the ska-punk band Operation Ivy. He was responsible for the band's energetic and politically charged lyrics on their sole album, *Energy* (1989). Following Operation Ivy's breakup, Michaels remained active in the music scene, forming the ska-punk group Common Rider in 1999 and engaging in other punk-related projects. In addition to his musical contributions, he is also a respected artist within the punk community, creating illustrations and paintings for albums and zines.

name: Tim Armstrong
description: Timothy Ross Armstrong (born Nov 25, 1965) is an American musician, songwriter, and record producer. He is best known as the co-founder, lead singer and guitarist of the punk rock band Rancid and a founding member of the rap-rock group Transplants. Armstrong previously played in the influential East Bay ska punk band Operation Ivy. In 1997 he co-founded Hellcat Records (a subsidiary of Epitaph Records) with Brett Gurewitz. He co-wrote Jimmy Cliff’s 2012 reggae album Rebirth, which won a Grammy. He remains an active member of Rancid, which has released ten studio albums and sold millions of records worldwide.

name: Matt Freeman
description: Matt Freeman (born April 23, 1966) is an American bassist and songwriter, best known as the co-founder and longtime bassist of the punk rock band Rancid. He and vocalist Tim Armstrong played together in East Bay bands including the ska-punk pioneers Operation Ivy before forming Rancid in 1991. Rancid’s success in the 1990s helped revive mainstream interest in punk rock, and the band has released ten studio albums. Freeman also leads the side project Devil’s Brigade (as singer and bassist). His playing, noted for fast, aggressive walking bass lines, earned him praise as 'one of punk’s most iconic bassists'.

name: Dave Mello
description: Dave Mello (born Feb 24, 1969) is an American drummer and songwriter, known primarily for his work with the hardcore ska-punk band Operation Ivy. He served as Operation Ivy’s drummer from the band’s formation in 1987 through their breakup in 1989. After the split, Mello and his brother Pat formed the punk band Downfall, while his former bandmates Tim Armstrong and Matt Freeman formed Rancid. He later co-founded the punk band Schlong. Mello remains active in the East Bay music scene, frequently performing with local bands at the 924 Gilman Street venue.

name: Rancid
description: Rancid is an American punk rock band that formed in Berkeley, California, in 1991. The band was founded by former Operation Ivy members Tim Armstrong (guitar/vocals) and Matt Freeman (bass/vocals), and the lineup also includes Lars Frederiksen (guitar/vocals) and Branden Steineckert (drums). Rancid rose to mainstream prominence in the mid-1990s with albums such as *Let’s Go* (1994) and *...And Out Come the Wolves* (1995), which featured popular singles like "Ruby Soho" and "Time Bomb". Over their three-decade career, the band has released ten studio albums, sold over four million records worldwide, and remains active.

name: Lars Frederiksen
description: Lars Erik Frederiksen (born Aug 30, 1971) is an American punk rock musician and producer. He is best known as guitarist and co-vocalist of the band Rancid. Frederiksen joined Rancid in 1993 and first appeared on their second album Let’s Go. He also fronts the street-punk band Lars Frederiksen and the Bastards, and plays in the ska-punk group Old Firm Casuals. In addition to performing, he has produced records for other punk bands (for example Dropkick Murphys). A California native, Frederiksen has been a prominent figure in punk since the early 1990s. He was also briefly a member of UK Subs in 1991.

name: Branden Steineckert
description: Branden Steineckert (born April 21, 1978) is an American drummer and songwriter. He is known as the drummer for the punk rock band Rancid. Steineckert was also a founding member and the original drummer of the post-hardcore band The Used. In 2006 he joined Rancid, replacing the band's longtime drummer Brett Reed, and has recorded multiple albums with the band, including Let the Dominoes Fall (2009). Steineckert grew up in Idaho and remains an active member of Rancid.

name: Brett Reed
description: Brett Reed (born July 12, 1972) is an American drummer best known as the original drummer of the punk band Rancid. He joined Rancid in 1991 (as Tim Armstrong’s roommate) and played on the band’s first five albums. In 2002 he joined bandmates Tim Armstrong and Matt Freeman in the side project Devil’s Brigade. Reed left Rancid in 2006 after 15 years of membership. He is noted for his tight, straightforward punk drumming on Rancid’s early records.

name: Blink-182
description: Blink-182 is a pop-punk band from Poway, California, formed in 1992. The band's classic lineup features Mark Hoppus on bass and vocals, Tom DeLonge on guitar and vocals, and Travis Barker on drums. They achieved massive success with albums like *Enema of the State* (1999) and *Take Off Your Pants and Jacket* (2001), which produced hit singles including "All the Small Things" and "What's My Age Again?". Known for their energetic live performances and irreverent humor, Blink-182 played a key role in popularizing pop-punk in the late 1990s. As of 2021, the band had sold over 50 million albums globally.

name: Mark Hoppus
description: Mark Allan Hoppus (born March 15, 1972) is an American musician, singer, and songwriter, best known as the bassist and co-vocalist of the pop-punk band Blink-182. He co-founded Blink-182 in 1992 and has appeared on every Blink-182 album. The band broke into the mainstream with hits like “All the Small Things” from Enema of the State (1999). After Blink-182’s hiatus in 2005, Hoppus co-founded the alternative rock band +44. Blink-182 reunited in 2009 and continue to record and tour. Outside of performing, Hoppus has produced records for other rock bands and co-founded clothing brands (Atticus, HiMyNameIsMark).

name: Tom DeLonge
description: Tom DeLonge (born Dec 13, 1975) is an American musician, songwriter, and entrepreneur. He is co-founder, guitarist, and co-lead vocalist of the pop-punk band Blink-182. DeLonge formed Blink-182 in 1992 with Mark Hoppus and Scott Raynor, and co-wrote many of the band’s hit songs. After Blink-182’s initial breakup in 2005, he founded the alternative rock project Angels & Airwaves in 2005. Blink-182 reunited in 2009, and DeLonge performed on two more albums before departing again in 2015. In recent years he has pursued filmmaking and founded the media company To the Stars, which researches UFO phenomena.

name: Travis Barker
description: Travis Barker (born Nov 14, 1975) is an American drummer and producer, widely known for his work in rock and punk. He has been the drummer for Blink-182 since 1998. Barker also co-founded the rock group +44 and has played in bands like Transplants and Box Car Racer. His versatile, high-energy drumming – blending punk, hip-hop and metal influences – earned him the nickname “punk’s first superstar drummer”. Barker survived a 2008 private jet crash that killed his friend DJ AM and returned to music, later releasing solo work and collaborating across genres.

name: Scott Raynor
description: Scott Raynor (born May 23, 1978) is an American musician, known as the founding drummer of Blink-182. He joined Blink-182 at age 14 in 1992 and played on the band’s early releases, including the demo Buddha (1994), and albums Cheshire Cat (1995) and Dude Ranch (1997). Raynor left Blink-182 in 1998 and was replaced by Travis Barker. After Blink-182, he played with other punk bands and later became a police officer in San Diego.

name: Matt Skiba
description: Matt Skiba (born Feb 24, 1976) is an American musician known as the lead singer, guitarist, and songwriter of the punk band Alkaline Trio. He co-founded Alkaline Trio in 1996 and has released ten albums with the band. Skiba also served as co-lead vocalist and guitarist for Blink-182 from 2015 to 2022, appearing on the albums California (2016) and Nine (2019). In addition, he led side projects such as Heavens and his solo backing band the Sekrets. Skiba’s lyrics often mix punk energy with dark, emotional themes.

name: Angels & Airwaves
description: Angels & Airwaves (AVA) is an American alternative rock band created in 2005 by Tom DeLonge during a break from Blink-182. The band's lineup includes DeLonge on vocals and guitar, David Kennedy on guitar, Ilan Rubin on drums, and Matt Rubano on bass. Their first album, *We Don’t Need to Whisper* (2006), climbed to number four on the Billboard 200 chart. DeLonge conceived AVA as a multimedia art project, resulting in the band releasing multiple albums that are accompanied by films and other visual media, all characterized by a spacey and cinematic sound.

name: David Kennedy
description: David Kennedy is an American guitarist known for his work with rock band Angels & Airwaves. He joined Angels & Airwaves in 2005 as lead guitarist and has appeared on all their albums. Earlier he played guitar in San Diego punk and hardcore bands including Hazen Street and Box Car Racer.

name: Ilan Rubin
description: Ilan Rubin (born 1988) is an American multi-instrumentalist and drummer. He joined Nine Inch Nails in 2008 and has been their touring drummer and songwriter since, helping the band earn a Rock Hall induction in 2020. In 2011 he became the drummer for Angels & Airwaves. Earlier he played drums for pop-punk band Fenix TX and Welsh rock band Lostprophets. Rubin also records solo material under the name The New Regime.

name: Matt Rubano
description: Matt Rubano is an American bassist and songwriter. He first gained recognition as the bassist for emo rock band Taking Back Sunday (2003–2010), appearing on albums including Where You Want to Be. In 2019 Rubano joined Angels & Airwaves as their bassist, recording on their later albums. He has songwriting credits from his time with Taking Back Sunday and continues touring with both bands.

name: Atom Willard
description: Atom Willard (born 1973) is an American drummer known for his work with punk and rock bands. He was the founding drummer of Angels & Airwaves (2005–2011) and earlier drummed for Rocket from the Crypt (1990–2000) and The Offspring (2003–2007). He later played with Social Distortion and was the drummer for Against Me! (2013–2020). Willard’s powerful style bridges hardcore punk and alternative rock.

name: Ryan Sinn
description: Ryan Sinn is an American bassist best known for his work with punk band The Distillers. He played bass on The Distillers’ second and third albums (2003–2005). In 2005 Sinn joined Angels & Airwaves as bassist and recorded on their debut album. He left Angels & Airwaves in 2007 and later rejoined The Distillers when they reunited in 2018.

name: Matt Wachter
description: Matt Wachter (born 1976) is an American bassist and keyboardist. He played bass and synth guitar for Thirty Seconds to Mars from 2001 to 2007, appearing on their early albums. In 2007 he joined Angels & Airwaves as bassist, contributing to albums like I-Empire and Love. Wachter remained with Angels & Airwaves until 2014, after which he retired from music.

name: Eddie Breckenridge
description: Eddie Breckenridge (born 1976) is an American bassist and founding member of rock band Thrice. He has played bass (and keyboards) on all of Thrice’s albums since their debut in 1998. In 2014 Breckenridge joined Angels & Airwaves for a period, appearing on the album Love: Part Two. He also formed the hardcore punk side project Less Art with his brother Riley.

name: Transplants
description: Transplants are an American punk/rap rock supergroup formed in 1999 by Tim Armstrong of Rancid and rapper Rob "Skinhead Rob" Aston. The lineup was later completed with the addition of Travis Barker on drums and Kevin Bivona on bass and keys. The band released their self-titled debut album, *Transplants*, in 2002, which included the single "Diamonds and Guns," followed by *Haunted Cities* in 2005. After a hiatus following their 2005 album, the group reunited in 2010 and released *In a Warzone* in 2013, continuing to blend punk rock with hip-hop influences.

name: Rob Aston
description: Robert "Skinhead Rob" Aston (born 1978) is an American rapper and vocalist. He is a founding member of rap-rock band Transplants, serving as co-vocalist with Tim Armstrong and Travis Barker. Aston is also the lead singer of D-beat punk band Death March and was part of hip-hop trio Expensive Taste. His style blends punk rock energy with hip-hop vocals.

name: Kevin Bivona
description: Kevin Bivona (born 1981) is an American musician and producer. He is the guitarist and keyboardist of ska-punk band The Interrupters, which he co-founded in 2011 with twin brothers. Bivona worked closely with Rancid’s Tim Armstrong, playing in Armstrong’s side projects and serving as a live touring guitarist. He has produced and engineered records for various punk acts and toured with other ska and punk bands.

name: Alkaline Trio
description: Alkaline Trio is an American punk rock band that originated in Chicago in 1996. The founding members were Matt Skiba (vocalist/guitarist), Rob Doran (bassist), and Glenn Porter (drummer). Dan Andriano replaced Doran in 1997, and the drummer position was later filled by Mike Felumlee and then Derek Grant starting in 2001. The band is known for its dark, melodic punk songs and has cultivated a dedicated fanbase. They have released several albums, including notable works like *Goddamnit* (1998) and *Crimson* (2005).

name: Dan Andriano
description: Dan Andriano (born 1977) is an American musician best known as co-lead singer and bassist of punk rock band Alkaline Trio. He joined Alkaline Trio in 1997 and has appeared on all their albums, providing melodic bass lines and vocals. Outside the band, Andriano records solo music as "Dan Andriano in the Emergency Room" and has toured with acts like Chuck Ragan.

name: Rob Doran
description: Rob Doran is an American bassist, notable for being the original bass player and backing vocalist of punk band Alkaline Trio. He played on the band’s early EP and their debut album Goddamnit! (1998). Doran left Alkaline Trio in 1997 to finish college and did not record with later lineups.

name: Glenn Porter
description: Glenn Porter is an American drummer known for his role in punk band Alkaline Trio. He was the band’s drummer from 1996 to 2000 and performed on their first two albums, Goddamnit! (1998) and Maybe I’ll Catch Fire (2000). Porter left the band after 2000 and has not recorded with other prominent groups since.

name: Mike Felumlee
description: Mike Felumlee is an American drummer, best known for his longtime work with Chicago’s Smoking Popes. He also played drums for Alkaline Trio from 1999 to 2001, appearing on From Here to Infirmary (2001), before returning to Smoking Popes. Felumlee co-founded the indie label Double Zero Records and has played in various punk and emo acts.

name: Derek Grant
description: Derek Grant (born 1977) is an American musician, best known as the drummer of Alkaline Trio from 2001 to 2023. He joined Alkaline Trio after Mike Felumlee’s departure and performed on every album from From Here to Infirmary onward. Earlier he played with The Suicide Machines. In the 2020s he also became a member of the rock band Dead Ending.

name: The Used
description: The Used is an American rock band that formed in Orem, Utah, in 2000. The band's current members are vocalist Bert McCracken, bassist Jeph Howard, drummer Dan Whitesides, and guitarist Joey Bradford. The founding lineup included McCracken, Howard, guitarist Quinn Allman, and drummer Branden Steineckert. The Used rose to prominence with emotionally charged albums such as *In Love & Death* (2004) and *Lies for the Liars* (2007). Their sound, which combines hardcore intensity with melodic hooks, has resonated with fans, and the band continues to be active with numerous albums and tours.

name: Bert McCracken
description: Bert McCracken (born 1982) is an American singer and songwriter, best known as the lead vocalist of post-hardcore band The Used. He co-founded The Used in 2001 and has sung on all their albums. McCracken co-wrote hits like "The Taste of Ink" and "All That I’ve Got". He is known for his intense, emotive vocal style and energetic stage presence.

name: Jeph Howard
description: Joseph "Jeph" Howard (born 1978) is an American musician known as the bassist and backing vocalist for rock band The Used. He co-founded The Used in 2001 and has played on every album. Howard’s bass lines drive the band’s blend of emo and post-hardcore. He also occasionally plays keyboards and contributes to songwriting.

name: Dan Whitesides
description: Dan Whitesides (born 1978) is an American drummer known for playing with rock band The Used since 2006. He joined after the original drummer left and has performed on all their albums from 2007 onward. Whitesides was active in several Utah rock bands before joining The Used. His solid drumming underpins the band’s melodic hard rock sound.

name: Joey Bradford
description: Joey Bradford (born 1984) is an American guitarist and backing vocalist. He is the co-lead guitarist of rock band The Used, joining in 2015 after the departure of Justin Shekoski. Bradford recorded on the band’s albums Imaginary Enemy and Heartwork and contributes to their songwriting. He previously played guitar in the metal band Mercykill and also produces music.

name: Quinn Allman
description: Quinn Allman (born 1980) is an American guitarist, best known as the founding lead guitarist of rock band The Used. He co-founded the band in 2001 and played on The Used’s first six albums. Allman’s guitar work helped define the band’s post-hardcore sound. He left The Used in 2015 and later formed the band Dead American.

name: Nine Inch Nails
description: Nine Inch Nails (NIN) is an American industrial rock band established in Cleveland, Ohio, in 1988 by Trent Reznor. For many years, Reznor was the sole official member until longtime collaborator Atticus Ross joined as a permanent member in 2016. NIN is celebrated for influential albums such as *Pretty Hate Machine* and *The Downward Spiral*. The touring version of the band has featured a rotating cast of musicians including guitarist Robin Finck, keyboardist Alessandro Cortini, and drummer Josh Freese. In recognition of their impact, Nine Inch Nails was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2020.

name: Paramore
description: Paramore is an American rock band that formed in Franklin, Tennessee, in 2004. The band was co-founded by lead vocalist Hayley Williams and drummer Zac Farro, with guitarist Taylor York joining in 2007. After signing with Fueled by Ramen, they released their debut album *All We Know Is Falling* in 2005. Paramore achieved mainstream success with albums like *Riot!* (2007) and *After Laughter* (2017), producing hit singles such as "Misery Business" and the Grammy-winning "Ain't It Fun". Bassist Jeremy Davis departed in 2015, while Zac Farro rejoined in 2017.

name: Taylor York
description: Taylor York, born in 1989, is an American guitarist and songwriter, best known as the lead guitarist of the band Paramore. He officially joined the band in 2007, becoming a core member alongside Hayley Williams. York has co-written many of Paramore's songs, including the Grammy-winning single "Ain't It Fun". He is credited with helping to broaden the band's musical style and has played on all of their albums since he joined.

name: All Time Low
description: All Time Low is an American pop-punk band formed in Towson, Maryland, in 2003. The band members are Alex Gaskarth (lead vocals, rhythm guitar), Jack Barakat (lead guitar), Zack Merrick (bass/backing vocals), and Rian Dawson (drums). All Time Low gained mainstream success in the mid-2000s with albums like So Wrong, It’s Right (2007) and Nothing Personal (2009).

name: Alex Gaskarth
description: Alex Gaskarth (born Dec 14, 1987) is an American musician, singer, and songwriter, best known as the co-founder, lead vocalist, and rhythm guitarist of the pop-punk band All Time Low. He has been the frontman of the band since its formation in 2003.

name: Jack Barakat
description: Jack Barakat (born Oct 18, 1988) is an American musician, known as the lead guitarist and backing vocalist of All Time Low. He has played with the band since 2003.

name: Rian Dawson
description: Rian Dawson (born Mar 22, 1985) is an American drummer, known as the drummer for All Time Low since the band’s formation in 2003.

name: Zack Merrick
description: Zack Merrick (born Mar 28, 1988) is an American bassist and musician, known as the bassist and backing vocalist of All Time Low since 2003.

name: Taking Back Sunday
description: Taking Back Sunday is an American rock band from Long Island, New York, formed in 1999. The original lineup featured vocalists Jesse Lacey and Adam Lazzara, guitarist John Nolan, bassist Shaun Cooper, and drummer Mark O'Connell. Lazzara became lead vocalist in 2001 and the band went on to release influential albums like Tell All Your Friends (2002) and Where You Want to Be (2004). Taking Back Sunday remains active, known for its catchy emo/alternative rock sound, and continues to tour and release new music.
